Class AbstractSchemesPanel<T extends Scheme,InfoComponent extends javax.swing.JComponent>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container

          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • com.intellij.application.options.schemes.AbstractSchemesPanel<T,InfoComponent>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The actual scheme type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDescriptionAwareSchemesPanel, SimpleSchemesPanel

    public abstract class AbstractSchemesPanel<T extends Scheme,InfoComponent extends javax.swing.JComponent>
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    Base panel for schemes combo box and related actions. When settings change, updateOnCurrentSettingsChange() method must be called to reflect the change in schemes panel. The method should be added to settings model listener.
    See Also:
    AbstractSchemeActions, SchemesModel, Serialized Form

      • getIndent

        protected int getIndent(T scheme)
        Returns an indent to calculate a left margin for the scheme name in the combo box. By default, all names are aligned to the left.
        Parameters:
        scheme - the scheme to calculate its indent
        Returns:
        an indent that shows a nesting level for the specified scheme

      • supportsProjectSchemes

        protected abstract boolean supportsProjectSchemes()
        Returns:
        True if the panel supports project-level schemes along with IDE ones. In this case there will be additional "Copy to Project" and "Copy to IDE" actions for IDE and project schemes respectively and Project/IDE schemes separators.
